        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "if you set locale to ar_SA it will have date array returns instead of integer, if you changed the locale to 'ar' or 'ar_JO' it will work normally.\r\n\r\nI got the following two lines code from magento 1.6.2:\r\n\r\n$filter = new Zend_Filter_LocalizedToNormalized(array('locale' => 'ar_SA'));\r\n$cartData[$index]['qty'] = $filter->filter(5);\r\n\r\n\r\nto fix this issue I have removed the following block from ar_SA.xml\r\n\r\n\r\n<decimalFormats>\r\n\t<decimalFormatLength>\r\n\t\t<decimalFormat>\r\n\t\t\t<pattern>#0.###;#0.###-<\/pattern>\r\n\t\t<\/decimalFormat>\r\n\t<\/decimalFormatLength>\r\n<\/decimalFormats>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nand everything worked normally now."
        },
